SIMPLE: under-age
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Under-age
<hw>Un"der-age`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not
having arrived at adult age; hence, incapable legally of performing
certain acts restricted to adults.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not having arrived at adult age, or at years of
discretion; hence, raw; green; immature; boyish; childish.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I myself have loved a lady, and pursued her with a great deal of
<qex>under-age</qex> protestation.</q> <rj><qau>J.
Webster.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Underagent</ent>⟦br⟧
